The paper discusses the development of a system for detecting and classifying marine mammal sounds using machine learning algorithms, which falls under the sub-category of Signal Processing (cs.SD). The use of deep learning approaches for this task suggests a focus on Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The integration of data scientists and biologists also suggests a potential focus on Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) for the development of new techniques for analyzing large-scale acoustic data.
